mcqs.question:
What will be the output of the following code?
int num = 0;
for(int i = 1; i <= 5; i++) {
 if(i == 3)
 break;
 num += i;
}
System.out.println(num);

What is the output?
int count = 0;
for(int i = 0; i < 5; i++) {
 if(i == 2)
 continue;
 count++;
}
System.out.println(count);

What is the output?
int sum = 0;
for(int i = 1; i <= 3; i++) {
 for(int j = 1; j <= 3; j++) {
 if(j == 2)
 break;
 sum += j;
 }
}
System.out.println(sum);

What is the output of this code?
public class Test {
 public static void main(String[] args) {
 int x = display();
 System.out.println(x);
 }
 static int display() {
 for(int i = 0; i < 3; i++) {
 if(i == 1)
 return i;
 }
 return 0;
 }
}

What is the output?
outer: for(int i = 0; i < 2; i++) {
 for(int j = 0; j < 2; j++) {
 if(j == 0)
 continue outer;
 System.out.print(j + " ");
 }
}

